Company: VoltaTech Solutions
Location: Milan, Italy (Hybrid)
Employment Type: Full-time
Seniority: Senior

About the Role
VoltaTech Solutions is looking for a Senior Electrical Engineer to join our R&D team in Milan. You will be responsible for designing and developing electrical systems for industrial automation products. This is a hands-on engineering role with direct impact on product development cycles.

Responsibilities

Design and develop electrical schematics and PCB layouts for industrial control systems
Lead technical reviews of electrical designs and provide guidance to junior engineers
Collaborate with mechanical and software teams to ensure system integration
Perform electrical testing, validation, and troubleshooting of prototypes
Ensure compliance with EU electrical safety standards (IEC, CE marking)
Manage component selection and BOM optimization
Write technical documentation and test reports
Support production team during manufacturing ramp-up


Required Skills

Power electronics design (AC/DC converters, motor drives)
PCB design using Altium Designer or KiCad
Embedded systems knowledge (STM32, Arduino, or similar)
Signal integrity and EMC/EMI analysis
MATLAB/Simulink for system modeling
Proficiency with oscilloscopes, multimeters, and lab equipment
Knowledge of IEC 61000, IEC 62368 safety standards

Nice to Have

Experience with PLC programming (Siemens, Rockwell)
Familiarity with CAN bus, Modbus, or industrial communication protocols
Experience with battery management systems (BMS)
Knowledge of functional safety (IEC 61508 / ISO 26262)


Requirements

Bachelor's or Master's degree in Electrical Engineering or related field
Minimum 5 years of experience in electrical/electronics design
At least 2 years in a senior or lead role
Fluent English (written and spoken)
Italian is a plus


What We Offer

Competitive salary: €55,000 – €75,000 depending on experience
Hybrid work: 3 days office, 2 days remote
25 days paid vacation
Training budget €2,000/year
Private health insurance
Relocation support for candidates outside Milan